text: hello
today we're going to show you how to
deploy a model trained in amazon
recognition custom labels
as well as perform inference using the
aws command line interface
this tutorial assumes you already have a
model trained with amazon recognition
custom labels
if you haven't already trained a model
please watch our other videos which show
you how to do so
here you can see we have a project that
we recently created called
home classify project you can also see
a model was trained in a sitting and
training completed stage
in order to use this model we need to
start it
and this can be done with python code or
by using the aws command line interface
today we will be using the latter from
the project screen
i'm going to click on the name of my
project
and then i'm going to click on the
specific model that i want to deploy
from this page i can scroll down to the
bottom of the page
and find the section titled use your
model
then i will expand the section labeled
api
code here you can find the listed
commands we will need to start the model
these commands will need to be run from
a command line with the aws command line
interface
or aws cli installed
an easy way to do this is to use aws
cloud shell
which is a browser-based command line
interface available right in the browser
this is available by clicking the
command line icon in the navigation page
of the aws console aws cloud shell
automatically is granted the same
permissions that you have when you log
into the console
you don't have to use aws cloud shell
and you can use the command line of your
choice but
aws cloud shell makes it easy so you
don't have to worry about installing any
tools
or downloading any credentials
now that we've got our command line up
and running we will return to the custom
labels page
and copy the command to start our model
then we paste this command into our
command line
accept the warning and hit enter
here we receive a response that our
model is starting
and if we go back to the model page and
refresh
we can see that our model is being
deployed model deployment usually takes
between
10 and 15 minutes
after a few minutes we can see that our
model has moved to
the running state which indicates our
model is ready to serve predictions
scrolling back down to the bottom of the
page we can see the command to
analyze an image this command contains
placeholder values for the s3 bucket
and object name and i've already
uploaded an image
of a living room to s3 as you see here
so i'm going to copy this command into a
text editor
replace the values for bucket name
and the file name including the path
and then i can copy this command into my
aws cloud shell environment
the model will analyze this image and
return a correct prediction for living
room
that's how you can deploy a model and
perform inference with amazon
recognition custom labels
check out our other videos if you want
to see how we created this data set
trained and evaluated our model thank
you
you
